      "comment": "PROUD MARY (4) was in the minors two back (22.61) at Ballarat but ran below best last time at Bendigo, finishing 6th. Should be very hard to beat this time. INVICTUS BLUE (6) has mixed form recently, finishing fifth (19.93) in a Grade 5 at Healesville latest but did run well two back when in the frame. Well placed here and can atone this time. SUDOKU CARMELLO (7) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (20.54) at Traralgon behind Redback Express in a Bottom Up - Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Has a solid record from this box including three wins and a minor placing. Must be included in calculations. JOAN'S GEM (3) should be thereabouts despite an unplaced run here most recently.",
